body_html:
I Tried it on processors : XEON W 3565 - Core i3 550 (both somewhat older models supposedly do not have avx) and on a Celeron 3930 : wikipedia Q1 2017 Kaby Lake supposedly having avx, no? (exactly same error _pywrap_tensorflow_internal // DLL load failed)
I tried also on a AMD FX(tm)-6300 ... and .... YES : we have a winner : it is an AVX problem - duplicate of #17386
Celeron 3930 was a bit doubt ... but aparently has NO avx ... the AMD-FX-6300 clearly has (as stated on the webpage of the processor.
Et voila, thank you gunan for putting me on the right track.
I have a bunch of Xeon's they gave me to play with, old ones, but still good enough to satisfy the guy in R&D with :-) .I'll use TF 1.5 or try the whl-solution mentioned in the other post
You should really document this thing, because it took me two days, just for nothing.
